<https://fairmat-nfdi.github.io/nomad-simulations/rdf/section/nomad_simulations.schema_packages.numerical_settings.KLinePath> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "KLinePath" ;
    rdfs:comment """A base section used to define the settings of a k-line path within a multidimensional mesh. The `points` and other k-space quantities are defined in units of the reciprocal lattice vectors, so that to obtain their Cartesian coordinates
value, one should multiply them by the reciprocal lattice vectors (`points_cartesian = points @ reciprocal_lattice_vectors`).""" ;
